#  Name:
#     kappa_ardplot_style.def

#  Purpose:
#     Defines the default style produced by the ardplot application.

#  Description:
#     This file contains default settings for plotting style attributes
#     to be used by ardplot. These defaults can be over-ridden by the user
#     by supplying a value for the STYLE parameter when running ardplot.
#     The defaults in this file over-ride the defaults in kappa_style.def.
#     See $KAPPA_DIR/kappa_style.def for more information on KAPPA style
#     files.

#  Notes:
#     -  Always include attribute axis qualifiers, etc, explcitly in this
#     file.  For instance, say "textlab(1)=1" and "textlab(2)=1" instead of
#     just "textlab=1".

#  Authors:
#     David S. Berry (STARLINK)
#     {enter_new_authors_here}

#  History:
#     14-OCT-1999 (DSB):
#        Original version.
